From cc7c33389acc0c7647d6798e56dd0b75b9273353 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Jake Teton-Landis <just.1.jake@gmail.com>
Date: Sun, 5 Jul 2026 05:10:51 -0400
Subject: [PATCH 21/25] Render lineage ids: stable per (root x batch-set), dead
 at commit/abandon
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Cosignal spec §4.1 fact 5, capability bit 1<<7. onRenderPassStart gains a
third argument: a positive-integer lineage id minted per (root x
batch-set) — the key Suspense thenable capsules need (spec §5.8). Every
pass over the same set reports the same id: restarts after an urgent
interrupt, replays, Suspense retries, and the fresh passes discardAllWip
re-schedules. A different set is a different id: a restart that rebases
in an extra batch, a fresh batch after commit, and the same spanning set
on two roots (per-root minting). Ids die at the first commit that takes
any of the set's lanes out of root.pendingLanes (commit or prune);
commits that leave the set fully pending (unrelated batches, the
mid-render re-pend split) do not kill it.

The key is the canonicalized included-token set PLUS the render-time
entangled lanes: tokens alone would alias unrelated token-free
transitions (no external write ever mints their token), lanes alone would
miss committedRoots lock-in set changes; lane recycling cannot alias
because reusing a live lane IS the merge rule and dead lanes' entries
died with their sets.

Also spec test 23 (Commit file): root container identities are stable
across every event kind, and a portal's updates classify, render, report,
and commit against the PARENT root's container — the portal target never
appears on the channel.

Tests: 6 new lineage tests (Pass file) + test 23 (Commit file); 40/40 on
all four channels; 15 upstream suites green; linc, prettier, flow
dom-node clean.
